# Kafka & Message Handling

## Topic Naming
- ✅ Name topics by event, not by consumers
- ✅ Use hierarchical naming: scope → event
  ```typescript
  // Good
  'aws.rds.new.clone'
  'aws.s3.new.bucket'
  'sql.schema.post.datastore'
  ```
- ✅ Include example producer/consumer in a `.kafka` file for new topics

## Message Interfaces
- ✅ Export `KafkaMessageInterface` instead of `KafkaTopic`
- ✅ Avoid implementing handlers that just forward messages between topics
  - Exception: Parallel processing prevention
- ✅ Use structured message interfaces with proper typing
